    {
      "id": "ev-3",
      "title": "Home & Heart: silya, pintuan, bintana, puso",
      "theme": "Furniture, house parts, and the heart",
      "intro": "The final lesson covers two pieces of furniture and two architectural features of the home, plus the most emotionally loaded word in Kapampangan — 'puso' (heart). 'Silya' (chair) and 'pintuan' (door) are from Spanish 'silla' and 'puerta'. 'Bintana' (window) comes from Spanish 'ventana'. 'Puso' (heart) appears in many expressions of love and pride, such as 'king puso ku' (in my heart). Learning these words lets you describe and navigate both the physical home and the emotional landscape.",
      "wordIds": [
        "ev-silya",
        "ev-pintuan",
        "ev-bintana",
        "ev-puso"
      ],
